dataIdInfo.idPurp: This dataset was developed by the USGS as part of the Phase 6 Land Use Project to support monitoring, modeling, and assessing the impacts of land use/cover change throughout the Chesapeake Bay watershed.
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
High-Resolution Land Use: Sixteen land use classes were mapped: 0 - Background, 1 - Impervious, Road, 2 - Impervious, Non-Road, 3 - Tree Canopy over Impervious, 4 - Water, 5 - Tidal Wetlands, 6 - Floodplain Wetlands, 7 - Other Wetlands, 8 - Forest, 9 - Tree Canopy over Turf, 10 - Mixed Open, 11 - Fractional Turf (small), 12 - Fractional Turf (med), 13 - Fractional Turf (large), 14 -Fractional Impervious, 15 - Turf Grass, 16 - Agriculture

The complete class definitions and standards can be viewed here: Definitions
dataIdInfo.idCredit: United States Geological Survey, Chesapeake Bay Program, Chesapeake Bay Program Land Use Workgroup, Chesapeake Conservancy, Conservation Innovation Center
